{#
  Defines a cert-manager ClusterIssuer of type 'ca' that signs downstream
  certificates with the homelab-ca key pair. The CA Secret it references
  is produced by cert-manager-homelab-ca-cert.yml.j2 and lives in the
  cert-manager namespace.

  Together with the selfsigned-issuer ClusterIssuer this completes the
  two-tier trust chain:

      selfsigned-issuer ─signs→ homelab-ca (Certificate, isCA: true)
                                    │
                                 homelab-ca-issuer (ClusterIssuer, type ca)
                                    │
                                    └─signs→ wildcard-tls, future certs

  Any future Certificate that wants to be trusted by operator devices
  should reference this issuer rather than the selfsigned-issuer.

  Variables:
    cert_manager_namespace:  Namespace where the homelab-ca Secret lives,
                             so the ca-type issuer can locate the
                             signing material.
#}
apiVersion: cert-manager.io/v1
kind: ClusterIssuer
metadata:
  name: homelab-ca-issuer
spec:
  ca:
    secretName: homelab-ca
